---
// src/pages/itad.astro — Specialized Authority Pillar for ITAD in Kochi
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { contact } from '../data/contact.js';
import { generateMassiveFaqs } from '../data/faqs.js';
import { locations } from '../data/locations.js';
import { services } from '../data/services.js';

const pageTitle = "ITAD Services Kochi | Certified Data Destruction & Corporate Decommissioning";
const pageDesc = "The ultimate 12,000+ word encyclopedia on IT Asset Disposition in Kochi. Learn about NIST 800-88, data sanitization, server retirement, and DPDP compliance.";

// Generate 200 High-Quality Local FAQs focused on ITAD
const faqs = generateMassiveFaqs("ITAD");

// Programmatic Content Generators for SEO Word Density
const chapters = [
  {
    title: "1. The Evolution of Corporate ITAD in Ernakulam",
    content: "IT Asset Disposition (ITAD) is no longer a localized logistics issue—it is a critical cybersecurity and legal mandate. As Kochi transforms into a premier IT destination with the expansion of Infopark and Smart City, the volume of decommissioned enterprise hardware has surged. Older practices of stockpiling retired assets in server rooms or selling them to unverified vendors now violate the strict provisions of the DPDP Act 2023. At EWaste Kochi, our certified ITAD protocols ensure that retiring server arrays, endpoint devices, and networking gear are treated with forensic-level security. We neutralize the catastrophic risks of data breaches that cost enterprises millions in regulatory fines and reputational destruction.",
  },
  {
    title: "2. The Anatomy of NIST 800-88 Data Sanitization",
    content: "When discussing hard drives, solid-state drives, and NVMe media, simply deleting files or reformatting the partition structure is utterly insufficient. Data remnants can be resurrected using accessible forensic tools. We deploy the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) Special Publication 800-88 Guidelines for Media Sanitization. Our purging mechanism involves multi-pass, cryptographic overwrites tailored specifically to the medium's architecture, including flash wear-leveling algorithms. When logical sanitization is deemed insufficient for categorized sensitive data, we proceed to physical destruction via industrial shredders, reducing the platter to localized metallic dust. Our post-operation audit generates an irrefutable, serialized Certificate of Destruction.",
  },
  {
    title: "3. Circular Economics: Maximizing Value Recovery",
    content: "End-of-life does not always mean End-of-Value. One of the primary focal points of an elite ITAD program is asset remarketing and lifecycle extension. For devices ranging from Dell PowerEdge servers to Apple MacBooks, EWaste Kochi employs a rigid grading matrix following R2v3 standards. Functional components are ethically refurbished, stripped of any residual organizational telemetry, and redeployed into secondary markets. This systematic value recovery mechanism subsidizes the cost of your ITAD engagement and drastically reduces the carbon footprint associated with fresh hardware manufacturing. A rigorous ESG report detailing the CO2 offset is provided to interlock with your corporate sustainability metrics.",
  },
  {
    title: "4. Navigating DPDP Act 2023 Compliance",
    content: "India's Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act of 2023 fundamentally alters how organizations handle retired technology. Under the act, corporations act as 'Data Fiduciaries'. A breach originating from a mismanaged end-of-life laptop constitutes a direct violation of the fiduciary duty, triggering penalties formulated up to ₹250 Crores. Engaging a certified ITAD partner is your only legal insulator. EWaste Kochi assumes the chain-of-custody via secure, documented logistics. By the time your hardware leaves the Infopark campus, its fate is mathematically documented. We indemnify our corporate partners by providing legally binding certificates, satisfying the most aggressive audits conducted by the RBI and SEBI.",
  },
  {
    title: "5. Comprehensive Logistics & On-Site Decommissioning",
    content: "Transporting retired data assets demands military-grade friction reduction. EWaste Kochi operates an elite logistics framework. From white-glove un-racking of blade servers within tier-3 data centers to GPS-tracked transport fleets deployed globally across Kerala, the integrity of the hardware is preserved. High-risk clients can opt for on-site shredding, where our mobile industrial units destroy hard drives within your parking perimeter, accompanied by CCTV verification and immediate digital receipt generation. We handle everything: cable mining, rack removal, sweep-out procedures, and environmental cleanup, allowing your IT staff to remain fundamentally focused on internal architecture."
  }
];

const massiveSubChapters = Array.from({ length: 50 }, (_, i) => ({
  title: `Sector ${i + 1}: Granular Analysis of IT Asset Disposition Strategies`,
  content: `In section ${i + 1} of this extensive ITAD analysis, we break down the nuances of verifiable hardware retirement. When scaling IT operations within Kerala's major commercial zones, treating hardware disposal as a core operational competency is critical. We meticulously reconcile every serial number—from Cisco core routers to individual NVMe clusters. The DPDP Act dictates stringent tracking; missing a single asset category ${i%20 + 1} item during a massive corporate refresh creates immense legal vulnerabilities. Our KSPCB-certified technicians, operating in areas like Kakkanad and Kochi city, provide a fully sealed chain of custody. We execute certified data wiping protocols and offer on-site physical destruction guarantees. Beyond risk mitigation, our advanced circular economy protocols reintegrate viable components back into the ecosystem, slashing scope-3 carbon emissions. ESG (Environmental, Social, and Governance) analytics are fully synthesized for our corporate ITAD partners. ` + chapters[i % 5].content
}));

const interlinks = [];
for(let i=0; i<locations.length; i++) {
  const matchingService = services.find(s => s.category === 'itad' || s.category === 'data');
  if(matchingService && interlinks.length < 200) {
    interlinks.push({
      title: `${matchingService.name} Logistics in ${locations[i].name}`,
      url: `/locations/${locations[i].slug}/${matchingService.slug}`
    });
  }
  // Alternate links to push 200 total
  const repService = services[i % services.length];
  if (interlinks.length < 200) {
    interlinks.push({
      title: `${repService.name} Corporate Setup in ${locations[i].name}`,
      url: `/locations/${locations[i].slug}/${repService.slug}`
    });
  }
}

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: 'https://ewastekochi.com/' },
  { name: 'ITAD Services', url: 'https://ewastekochi.com/itad' },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDesc}
  faqs={faqs}
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <Navbar currentPath="/itad" />

  <section class="section pillar-hero" style="background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(5,9,8,0.85), var(--bg)), url('/img/itad_hero_premium.png'); background-size: cover; background-position: center;">
    <div class="wrap" style="position: relative; z-index: 2;">
      <p class="sec-eyebrow" style="color: var(--blue); background: rgba(0,0,0,0.5); padding: 5px 15px; border-radius: 20px;">Enterprise ITAD Architecture</p>
      <h1 class="sec-title" style="text-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.8);">IT Asset Disposition: <br/>The <em>Complete</em> Guide</h1>
      <p class="sec-sub" style="color: var(--white); font-weight: 500; text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.9);">
        The definitive 12,000+ word database mastering enterprise data sanitization, secure logistics, DPDP Act 2023 alignment, and scalable hardware decommissioning in Kerala.
      </p>
      <div class="p-cta-btns" style="margin-top: 40px; justify-content: flex-start;">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" style="background: var(--blue); color: white;">Request ITAD Audit</a>
        <a href="#massive-content" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg" style="color: var(--white); border-color: var(--white);">Explore The Encyclopedia</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-alt" id="massive-content">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="wiki-grid">
        <div class="wiki-main">
          {chapters.map((chap, idx) => (
            <article class="wiki-chapter">
              <h2>{chap.title}</h2>
              <p>{chap.content}</p>
            </article>
          ))}
          
          <div class="wiki-deep-dive">
            <h2 class="sub-h" style="color: var(--blue); margin-top: 60px;">Deep Dive Analytics: 50 ITAD Case Studies</h2>
            {massiveSubChapters.map((chap) => (
              <div class="deep-dive-block">
                <h3>{chap.title}</h3>
                <p>{chap.content}</p>
                <p class="seo-density"><em>Keywords context: IT Asset Disposition in Kochi, NIST 800-88 data destruction Kerala, Server decommissioning Ernakulam, Enterprise SSD destruction.</em></p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="wiki-sidebar">
          <div class="sticky-box">
            <h3>200+ Local Corporate ITAD Hubs</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; margin-bottom: 20px; color: var(--muted);">Explore certified local compliance zones designed for massive enterprise workflows in Kerala.</p>
            <ul class="interlink-list scrollbar-custom">
              {interlinks.map((link) => (
                <li>
                  <a href={link.url}>
                    <span class="icon" style="color: var(--blue);">➔</span> {link.title}
                  </a>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

      <div class="massive-faq-container">
        <h2 class="sub-h text-center">200 High-Authority Questions on IT Asset Disposition</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          {faqs.map((f, i) => (
            <div class={`faq-item ${i === 0 ? 'open' : ''}`}>
              <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded={i === 0 ? "true" : "false"}>
                <span class="faq-qt">{f.q}</span>
                <span class="faq-ic" style="color: var(--blue);">+</span>
              </button>
              <div class="faq-a">
                <div class="faq-at">{f.a}</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .pillar-hero { padding: 160px 0 100px; text-align: left; position: relative; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border); }
  .pillar-hero::before { content:''; position: absolute; inset:0; background: radial-gradient(circle at 70% 50%, transparent, rgba(5,9,8,1) 80%); z-index: 1; }
  .wiki-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 350px; gap: 60px; margin-bottom: 80px; }
  .wiki-chapter { margin-bottom: 50px; }
  .wiki-chapter h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 20px; color: var(--blue); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 10px; }
  .wiki-chapter p { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); font-family: var(--serif); text-align: justify; }
  .deep-dive-block { margin-bottom: 40px; padding: 30px; background: rgba(0,180,255,0.03); border-left: 3px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; }
  .deep-dive-block h3 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-bottom: 15px; color: var(--white); }
  .deep-dive-block p { font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .seo-density { font-size: 0.75rem !important; color: var(--muted) !important; opacity: 0.6; }
  .sticky-box { position: sticky; top: 120px; background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 30px; border-radius: 20px; }
  .interlink-list { list-style: none; max-height: 800px; overflow-y: auto; padding-right: 10px; }
  .interlink-list li { margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .interlink-list a { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text); padding: 8px 12px; background: var(--surface); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid transparent; transition: 0.2s; line-height: 1.4; }
  .interlink-list a:hover { border-color: var(--blue); color: var(--white); background: rgba(0,180,255,0.05); }
  .scrollbar-custom::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 4px; }
  .scrollbar-custom::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: var(--bg); }
  .scrollbar-custom::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--blue); border-radius: 2px; }
  .massive-faq-container { margin-top: 100px; padding-top: 100px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .wiki-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .sticky-box { position: static; max-height: none; }
    .interlink-list { max-height: 400px; }
  }
</style>
